Virginia Tech, a serene university in Blacksburg, was rocked by a tragic shooting that claimed 32 lives.
The campus, nestled in the Blue Ridge mountains, is the heart of the town.
The university's history dates back to 1872, focusing on practical education.
The shooting unfolded in a dorm and an engineering building, causing panic and chaos.
The FBI ruled out terrorism as the cause.
President Bush attended a memorial service to honor the victims.
The incident, the deadliest in US history, led to the cancellation of classes for the week.
It was a day of mourning for the nation.
